Really liked this one. Everything feels plausible, particularly the tea itself. At first I thought it would just give the drinker the ability to more easily bend reality, but the probability approach is simultaneously more interesting and more reasonable. Both the Foundation and Dr. Singh are both acting in the best interest of everyone around them, and frankly this SCP has what's probably the happiest ending I've seen.







